And very reasonably priced...

This case is very well designed (Galaxy S2, AT&T I777). It does what it is meant for. It fits perfectly and leaves no gaps. Pretty stiff, yet flexible, just right. The material does not feel cheap at all, compared to even the $20 ones. It prevents the phone from slipping and does not stick to pocket insides. Pure black in color and it has a nice Carbon-fibre rough texture on the back. This one also protects the phone and is not so thick as to take away the slim beauty of your galaxy s2.
It is a great cover, value for money. Fits perfectly in the hand and got the right kind of protection.
This is one of the better tpu cases for samsung i9100. It fits the phone perfectly and feel very solid. It looks like a hard case but actually very flexible.

I would recommend getting this case from the Electromaster vendor if you bought the original AT&T; Samsung Galaxy SII (SGH-i777), which is NOT the Skyrocket version. Other vendors may have different molds, thus why some reviewers are complaining about needing to cut extra holes or widening holes.This is a wonderful TPU case. For less than $3, the case fits all the needs I have for my new phone. It has the right holes on all sides and I didn't need to cut any holes out for the top mic nor the microusb jack at the bottom, as different sized microusb cables fit perfectly. As others have previously mentioned, it feels like the rubber from a rollerblade wheel and is very shiny. It also attracts fingerprints, but they wipe away very easily.As for the weight and "bulkiness", the case did not add any noticeable weight to the phone; while the case does slightly add to the thickness of the walls of the phone, it is a snug fit and almost felt like nothing was increased in size.I will try to record a video for this case later today and update this review.
summary: Perfect for ATT SGH-i777 (from Electromaster vendor)

reviewText: I ordered this case for the Samsung Galaxy S2 - ATT version.  Ordered on Saturday; it arrived on Friday.The case was a bit too snug for this phone so it didn't wrap around completely to the front face on all 4 edges of the phone. It would work but it isn't quite right. The case I ended up using is a Great Shield which does this properly.This case is also very slick which I didn't really like. The upper right corner of the case has a cutout but there doesn't appear to be a reason for it on my phone (beside the headphone jack cutout but over on the corner). Therefore this corner of the phone is not fully protected which I didn't like since I think the phone is most likely to hit on a corner if dropped. Overall, I won't be using this case.
summary: Case is OK but didn't fit well; I won't be using it.

reviewText: It's a slim and sleek case. It a rubbery but shiny case and you can kind of see finger prints. Seems like it protects the corners of the phone well. This item may work for other versions of the Samsung Galaxy S2 (and the packaging says it's compatible for the i9100) but it does not match for the Sprint Epic 4G Touch Samsung Galaxy S2 i9100 phone. The openings in the case do not match up with the phone, specifically the volume controls, ear phone jack, and power button. It they would have matched, then this case would have been nice as it would keep the phone profile slim while protecting the phone. Unfortunately, had to return it.

The skin case maintains the thinness of the galaxy phone, while rendering it safe from occasional drops. I had a problem with the cut out hole for the charger. I had to enlarge the hole with a razor; otherwise you are left with having to remove the skin each time you intend on charging your device. Besides that, the skin is great.

So I gave this a moderate review as the quality isn't too shabby, but beware that this doesn't work on the Samsung Galaxy S2 from Sprint. I should have paid more attention, it's totally not the fault of the seller.Pros - It's black and shiny.Cons - I'm an idiot.
summary: Doesn't Work on the Samsun Galaxy S2 from Sprint

That's according to Nexus/Samsung.  So, I emailed the seller and had GREAT support, should have just checked my manual or forums but this thing does 4K, well my stuff is only 1080p/3D and that's less than half the quality of 4k I guess!Issues.1.  So, first, my cable didn't work, had to use a better HDMI Cable.2.  My stereo downsizes things or upscales, but how can it downsize 4k, it doesn't even know what that is.  Had to upgrade software, then restart with SlimPort attached.  Worked better.3.  Did NOT work on my LG TV , Plasma 3D.  Worked on my Samsungs.**If you have issues, I suggest this.-  Try a DIRECT connection to your TV, if fails, try another cable.-  Make sure you have it powered, use your power cord to verify full power is getting to the TV.-  Try another brand TV with another HDMI cable, ccalbe can be the issue, so can TV. A Gain, Nexus issue, NOT adapter.
summary: Almost gave a 1 star, then user error, cable error, tv error, and Nexus issues were found, a Solid 5 STAR!

Very satisfied with my purchase. The quality is good and the shipping is quick. The case provides enough friction to enable a good grip on the phone. TPU (the plastic material where the case is made of) virtually resists oil and dust. I used to have an Otter box for my other phone. The protection is excellent BUT the silicone attracts dust like crazy. The S-Style pattern at the back is more of a personal taste - some people like it but some other may not. To me it adds some flavor to an otherwise plain black case. The protection on all 4 sides on the front panel looks sufficient (anyone dare to slam your phone on the floor to test it out?). I wish the top margin (above the earphone) can wrap down by a few mm. Overall I feel my phone secured in the case.

The cover around the volume key and the power key is stiff to prevent accidental activation, but not stiff to the point where it's hard to push when you mean it.Are there better cases out there, I have no doubt.  However at this price point I'm more than satisfied.

The plastic cover was so shiny I picked my teeth after eating a delicious blue crumble rare ny strip steak while staring deep into the sockets of someone I like to imagine is our dead pirate mascot George. reviewText: This pouch fits the EVO with no room to spare vertically. The BB Torch is shorter so there's a little extra space. The material is slightly thick, which should provide some protection, but may be just a bit bulky. My GF keeps both in her purse and now thinks the pouches are perfect (but not at first). I think it's the right balance b/t protection and bulk for non-pocket transport. Keeping the headset/wired handsfree with phone makes it a snug fit and lumpy. The see-through mesh material allows you to see the caller/screen without having to pull the phone out. The attached neck strap and drawstring are useful when needed.
summary: Fits BB Torch and HTC EVO

You need at least a 2 amp or 10w charger for the nexus. Otherwise the charger will just slow the discharge of the nexus.  HTC charger is good for charging devices with less demand.

This charger is NOT for the Nexus 10 ... it will BARELY charge if left plugged in overnight with no use. After 12 hours plugged in, my battery had increased from 6% to 18%. Not exactly "fast acting".  Furthermore, after being charged onerous shipping (nearly $8 from Denver to KC) by one of Amazon's illustrious third party sellers, I'm having a heckuva time getting a refund.  My best recommendation is to avoid this product and this third party seller. As this is my first experience with an Amazon third party seller, I may be avoiding ALL of them in the future.

I bought this skeptical as the other reviews above me were all negative, it is my second purchase of the same item (bought elsewhere) because I blew that one up by using to high of power plug, and I found it here cheaper.  Also, my cousin actually works for Samsung in South Korea and said yes, THIS WILL IN FACT WORK on the S4, the S4 was designed to be compatible with this.As all buyers above, I also had a choice, I could buy this one and save a LOT of money because it is 3 months old and also works on the S3, Note 2, and S4 (it will also work on the Note 3 by the way according to my cousin).  OR, buy the $50+ one that currently only ships from the UK, that is part number ET-H10FAUWEGWW.  That is the newest one that works on the S4 and doesn't require power by the way, but you pay for it and it's in white, I wanted a black one.Anyway, it works.  Here is how I did it.1.  Phone Off, TV OFF.2.  Plug in everything to adapter (phone and hdmi cable) and make sure Micro-USB power cord that is 1A or 1,000ma or you burn it out. Plug into TV.  I used a 2.1 amp one, blew out my first one.  Don't do that! =)3.  Turn on TV FIRST, set to right HDMI input, on AUTO, 60Hz if you have that option.  On my older TV, I had to use 720p and 60Hz so try that if you have issues.  **I think doing this first is necessary so the phone can see a TV signal and "sync" up to device correctly the first time.4.  Turn on phone.5.  Works.6.  For live view or proof as approved by over 5,000+ views on Youtube, search for video of a gentlemen in an orange shirt called "Samsung Galaxy S4: Connecting HDTV /MHL Adapter EPL-3FHU Through HDMI Port"Hope this helps, this is my first review and I find it odd that SO many are having issues with this.**UPDATE**I have the S4 on ATT by the way.  But, have also tested it on my neighbors S4 on Verizon, it took two restarts while plugged into everything to sync up but worked.  He said Verizon has an Android issue with video out that the next software update will fix, maybe that was the issue so he suggested to those with Verizon S4 be patient and wait for the next Android update from Verizon due in July 2013.  He'll be buying this on next.
summary: This works, was skeptical, but it works and saves you $30!!  Directions Below!

If you are looking at this product, be very careful.  This Amazon item is one of the top search results when looking for an MHL adapter for a Samsung Galaxy S4.  The item heading says it is for the Galaxy S4/SIV, and nowhere in the heading does it mention the S3/SIII.  Yet, when I received this item the box was clearly marked that this MHL adapter is for the S3.  If you read the other reviews, you will find that this has happened to everyone else as well.  The item description also states that this adapter will work on the S4 and s3.  It may work on the S3, who knows, but it does NOT work on the S4 as stated!  I have tried to use this MHL adapter on  multiple televisions using different HDMI cables/ports, and I have tried using my Samsung GS4 retail charger, a Samsung OEM S4 travel charger, and generic chargers.  No configuration has been able to get this item to work on the S4.  Every time my GS4 gives a message that it is "unable to mirror due to hardware failure."  I have a different MHL adapter that works just fine.  So I know the problem is not with any other components.  It appears that everyone posting reviews has had the same problems and has been unable to get this item to work on the S4.  This item simply does not work.  You have been warned.  If you ignore these reviews and buy this item, then do not complain when it does not work and you have to return it.Buy your MHL adapter elsewhere.*** UPDATE ***I purchased my item from the seller "ConneVity." I asked for authorization to return the item and get a refund.  (Most sellers would just approve the authorization, I would ship the item, and they would refund my money.  Not so easy in this case.) ConneVity, to their credit, was very prompt in their responses and their communications were very polite.  However, they were not very helpful.  I feel like I was getting the run-around.  When I asked for a refund they offered an exchange.  They tried to explain to me that the old S3 MHL adapters are the same as the new S4 MHL 2.0 adapters, just that the packaging is different.  When I pointed out how incorrect that was, ConneVity responded with reasons why the old S3 MHL adapter was useful.  Such as how the old S3 adapter can be used on the new S4 and the older S3.  I pointed out that I still wanted a refund because I don't have an S3 and it does NOT work with my S4.  Initially, ConneVity also tried to tell me that nothing was wrong with the item and it was the settings in my S4 that had to be changed.  Twice they said the S4 is not set up to mirror using MHL by default.  I pointed out how that was not true.  My other MHL adapter mirrors with no setting changes, just plug-and-play.  All the video and written tutorials online also demonstrate how the S4 mirrors using MHL by just plugging in the adapter.  I even linked to a written tech tutorial.  Finally, ConneVity admitted that it sounded like the MHL adapter I got was bad.  Now this is when things went from bothersome to truly aggravating.  ConneVity sent me an email containing the following procedure for obtaining a refund."Requires 100% feedback so I can prove to Amazon it works andthey let me force full refunds for future customers.  Then, I email aprepaid label, you return it, email when sent in the mail and I'll issuea full 100% refund, no Amazon penalty, refund issued within 2 businessdays of return shipping confirmation."They require that I give them 100% (positive?) feedback in order to get a full refund on an item that does not work.  They say that I need to prove to Amazon that the item works in order to get a refund when I am returning the item BECAUSE it does not work.  (And no one who left a review has been able to get this item to work on the S4.)  They seem to imply that otherwise I will be penalized by Amazon.  Is that a threat?  You read the message and decide for yourself.  Either way, I do not trust this seller so I went directly to Amazon to verify the truth of the procedure given to me.  I just wanted to know if any of this was actually true.  The Amazon representative who responded was kind enough to file one of Amazon's "A-Z Guarantee" claims for me and is contacting the seller directly!  Amazon also filed a claim with their Seller investigation team because ConneVity's return policy violates Amazon's community rules.At one point, ConneVity was even signing their emails as "Amazon.com for ConneVity" to make it look like I was actually dealing with Amazon employees.  Amazon representatives assured me the person I was talking with was the seller.  Just constant tricks and dishonesty.Just trying to save everyone else a headache.***UPDATE***Again, seller was ConneVity.  Amazon issued a full refund in the form of a gift card, told me to throw out the adapter, stop all communication with the seller, and let Amazon handle it.  (Amazon can always be trusted to do the right thing for customers.  Thank you Amazon.)  Yet seller still contacted me and tried to trick/scare me into editing and removing my feedback.  I contacted Amazon, and Amazon representatives informed me that pretty much everything the seller told me was false.  Sara, ConneVity's owner, emailed me that ConneVity (and I paraphrase) "deserves better feedback under Amazon's feedback agreement and Amazon expects me to remove or edit my feedback."  Amazon confirmed there is no such thing as a "feedback agreement" and I do not have to remove or edit anything.  In fact, the Amazon representative filed another claim with Amazon's seller investigation team because ConneVity's communications violated Amazon's community rules.ConneVity spent 3 paragraphs trying to make me feel guilty and trick me into removing my negative (but deserved) feedback.  Long-story-short, Amazon assured me nothing ConneVity said was true.  Amazon said the communication was cause for investigation and could be cause for ConneVity's removal from Amazon.  Most importantly, be very careful when dealing with this seller.  I advise just shopping elsewhere.
summary: BUYER BEWARE - POSTING IS A LIE!

reviewText: While this cable works fine for connecting your blackberry to your computer, it takes forever to charge your backberry. I'm not sure why, but it takes almost 5x longer than the original USB cable. IMO not worth the money.

A note of caution from someone who owned and used just about every major Blackberry model: if you already own a standard USB 2.0 cable and you don't need an extra, then you do NOT need this cable. All a Blackberry needs for data transfer is a STANDARD USB 2.0 cable with a Micro-USB connector at one end.There is NOTHING special about this cable and nothing justifies the artificially inflated MSRP listed for it. While this item is sold at a 90% off the MSRP discount, it's probably okay to purchase one, for as long as, after reading the first paragraph you decide that you will need a USB 2.0 cable.The items has 2 stars taken away for the exaggerated marketing claim (professional grade custom cable) and for the inflated MSRP.NOTE: Please make sure that you buy cable with a MICRO-USB connector because this is what your Blackberry needs.

I liked the idea of having a USB outlet for the car charger and the socket outlet adapter.This way you can use any USB cable to charge your Blackberry and you can leave the car adapter in the car without any dangling cables here and there in your car. I keep a USB cable in my laptop bag which is virtually almost with me anywhere I go. The plastic of both adapters is excellent but the USB cable felt a little bit cheap and thin that's why I use my own cable for charging. However I have tested it and it still does the job of charging the phone.One advice you may want to know, if you want to use the USB port in your computer to charge the phone, make sure it is a POWERED USB port and not a normal port.I used to know that all USB ports are powered since we can hook external hard drives (without power adapters) and they work by drawing power from USB. But when i used it to charge my phone at work, the battery indicator never went up it actually remained as it is for the whole 9 hours at work even tho I used the phone a lot. After investigating, I later discovered that in order to charge your blackberry thru a USB port, the port should be labeled POWERED as to indicate it got an extra electrical power extended into them. This is required for more demanding USB powered devices such as charging your Blackberry.However, if you use a normal USB port to plug your Blackberry, as said above, it will NOT charge the phone's battery, but in the same time the battery will hold its charge at its current level, which is EXCELLENT if you know that your battery won't survive the 9 hours at work and it only have enough charge for the trip back home from work.  This way you keep the battery level as it is and save the battery power for the trip back home :)

reviewText: Don't understand why the cell phone industry must continue to modify its charging connection (except for capitalistic reasons of course) When this happens, it is nice have have a resource such as this seller. Great product, price, shipping and service.

This was my first experience with an emergency charger so I don't have any baseline comparison.I ordered this charger as soon as I saw how quickly battery life on the Palm Pre Plus could be sapped. When it came it didn't work but I contacted the seller who sent out a free replacement that works fine (apparently the not working is a known issue).The charger does not come with instructions which provided a further challenge. Here's what I was told by the seller about using the device properly:Place the battery in with the + side facing the plug that inserts into the phone and you should see a light turn on quickly to indicate it's ready.  Then, plug it into the phone (preferably with the phone turned off) and wait up to 3 minutes until the light goes on again to indicate it is done charging.  Repeat, some phones will take up to 4 AA batteries to complete a full charge on a near 0% battery life battery.I haven't tried charging the phone completely with this charger, but it did bring the phone up from 90% to 100% with one battery and no problems once I got the replacement and had the right instructions.
I bought about 3 of these and on 1 the retraction action stopped working, but the other 2 are still going strong. I've had them for several years now.
This is the best car charger that I have ever owned.  I like the fact that you can leave the charger plugged in without the cord draped over the passenger seat.

I bought this charger for my HTC Driod Incredible the charger is a great price and the retractable cord is awesome, no bulky cords sitting in the glove box. However I used it for the 1st time yesterday for the 20 minute ride from work to school and while it charged quick (almost full),the problem I had was when I went to unhook my phone the unit itself was extremely hot! Couldn't hold it in my hand for more then a few seconds. Maybe the Incredible pulls too much power with the faster processor in it compared to the other Driods or I got a defective one but I would not suggest this charger if you are on the go a lot and would need to use the car charger frequently!
This item works very well. Love the fact that it is long and not curly. It makes it so much easier to use! Retraction is by far my favorite feature!!!

Works like a champ; the retractable cord makes this much smaller to store than previous chargers; the push button cord retract is reliable compared to the pull-and-release retraction types; the price is very reasonable (well under $10).  We have one for each device-type we need to charge in both cars.

I'm always concerned whether the moving parts of inexpensive products will work reliably.  This one does.  It charges my droid like my other chargers.  It recoils when I push the button.  It has a handy light that indicates when the unit is getting 12v.  I'm very happy.

This charger is really cool. My old charger had a long spiral cord that I hated because I couldn't drive with it dangling so I would put it in the back then I would loose it and it was just always such a big ordeal. This charger is so good, it is well worth every penny, and it has other phone jack things that go into it so if I get a new phone it might fit even if it has a different plug in.
Item did not work at all.  I should have known for less than $5 and no shipping that it was too good to be true.

Love this ... no cords hanging to get tangled .... love the device.  It's small and the retractable cord zips right back in at the touch of a button.  Wish ALL were like this, but unfortunately won't be useing it ...since I REALLLY dislike the New Palm and returned it!  They took away the tap screen for the phone ... AND the hot sync!  Bummer!Hope maybe this works on another phone?
Love the retractable cord on the car charger. Had a problem and vendor replaced immediately! Thank you
This product worked for about two weeks, now it works on and off. the convenience factor is great, but it won't stay in the cigarette lighter and works its way out very easily.
This is a great product. The retractible feature is great. Shipping didn't take long. It even has a little light that lights up things underneath it. I would recomend buying it.

I ordered this in May along with one for a Blackberry. They both were the same charger eventhought this one was priced a couple cents more. If your phone is near dead this charger does nothing for it. Now it does not work at all. Not worth it.

reviewText: This is great to keep in your purse or coat, it weighs about the weight of a AA battery. Sometimes you forget to charge your phone, I know I do all the time. And, by the time you realize it, you don't have the time to stop and charge it. This is perfect, all you have to do is pop a regular AA battery in it and it gives your phone a full charge, while you are on the go.
this is a very good product for the price. this is $19.99 in the t mobile store.

reviewText: I wanted a second charger that I could travel with and not take the OEM unit from home. After shopping around I found lots of options and lots of junk that either did not fit my phone and were supposed to or were more trouble to take along than the OEM unit. I took the plunge and ordered from A Days Tech. And from there it got better. When I got the unit which arrived neatly packaged in a padded envelope I contacted them about a fitment question I had and I was quite surprised to not only get an immediate answer but options as well. One would think charging your phone battery would not be that complicated but if you think about what it took to build that phone just try and make one at home and since little computers control battery charging its not as simple as charging the battery for your tractor. The charger operation is straight forward as its plug and play. The customer service is what I found to be unique. These guys could have taken my simple question as an annoyance and said plug it in and go away but instead I got a very nice summary for charging from the car adapter, ac adapter, and the USB adapter off the computer.In the future I will order more parts and pieces here just because I like these guys.

summary: Problematic service by vendor (sending car charger incompatible with Motorola T505 phone, and more) calls for a poor rating.

I was very disappointed and threw it away.  I had a reetractable cell phone charger for several years, but that recently also developed a short in the tiny cord from the charger to the phone - the tiny retractible cords are just not heavy duty enough (I guess).  However, the 3 month period this charger lasted was NOT worth the purchase - would not recommend it.Old write up:  I purchased this retractable chargers for my GPS off Amazon.  Is is perfect - Initially I was concerned because it felt a little cheap - however - that does not seem to be a problem.  Once it is plugged into the car, it won't be taken out - so doesn't matter if it "feels" cheap -  what matters is functionality.  I really purchased this charger for is the small diameter retractable cord that goes only from the charger to the GPS - I have a retractable corded charger for my cell phone and I absolutely love it - so I bought this and I love it just as much.  It is just what I was looking for.  Instead of a thick, long cord that you have to tie up with twist ties to make it look neat and out of the way, you have only the very narrow cord from the GPS to the charger...no extra ugly cord on the dash hanging down on the floorboard or console, getting tangled, etc.  This is perfect - just perfect.  I am delighted with the seller and the product.  Thank you.

This product falls under the category of "worth a try". It is tiny, sleek, and very pretty. It gives my phone about 10 minutes of charge for the price of an ordinary AA battery. The adapter fit the micro-usb port and the phone said it was charging, but I couldn't see any difference in the charging meter. Finally, thinking "it must do SOMETHING" I drained the phone completely, so it turned itself off. Then popped a fresh AA battery into the charger and plugged it in. Red LED light came on. Left it plugged in for an hour. Powered the phone on. The phone had about 10 minutes of charge, playing Scrabble, which is admittedly power-intensive, before it turned itself off again. So, I'm thinking this must be for the older, smaller phones, not my Samsung Mesmerize, or probably any screen-intensive phone. Oh well. I hope it didn't hurt the phone! Shipping and handling from this third-party seller is not refundable and I would have to pay to return it, so I'd only get about $4 back from my $15. I'm moving on to the AA tiny charger and we'll see how that works:[...]

reviewText: I found the BlueAnt Supertooth 3 wireless cell phone hands free device completely user friendly, providing controllable volume for entire car front and back seat occupants. It was priced right and easy to install and operate and out of the way. A great hands free dvice.

I contacted the seller of this item for my BlueAnt Supertooth 3 wireless device. I explained to them that the home charger that's displayed above, was shipped to my home. Well, imagine my surprise when the items that Amazon suggested in a combo did not fit my BlueAnt device. Well, So I took a chance and ordered the combo items per Amazon recommendation and of course I was upset because this is something that was recommended to me. I left a message for the seller and they responded that, if I don't notify them of my problem than they couldn't rectify the situation. Well, I reached out to the company in hopes of satisfying the customer (me). He/she asked me what model device I purchased, and I responded to their question thinking they'd contact me, and that's been over 2 weeks ago and still I'm stuck with this charger and NO solution to the problem. Although the charger didn't fit my BlueAnt device, at least it fits my daughters cell phone. Will not be ordering from this company anymore.

I purchased this product to have optional fast charging capability for my Zen X-fi.  Unfortunately, when I plugged this unit into the wall and attached my x-fi, the unit light came on and the x-fi charging routine started.  After about a minute, the x-fi charging light went out and didn't come aback on!  Oh, oh!  Power surge?  What?  I then plugged the x-fi into my PC USB port and was able to charge it up that way.  Whew!  It's a couple of days later and the x-fi seems to be OK.  But I wouldn't recommend this wall charger.  Buy a unit that is able to handle the power and convert it properly, giving the x-fi a clean power feed.  As a side note, when I was researching to contact the seller, I read through the seller comments, and there was someone who had a cell phone that was fried from a bad wall charger.  Another note:  when I contacted the seller, I received a prompt and courteous response and was able to get a refund on this product.
The product came as promised and when promised.  It works like it is supposed to.  I have absolutely no problems.

If you try a different charger, the headset simply will not charge.  I had purchased a used S9-HD at a garage sale and it did not have the requisite charger. reviewText: I bought this for a Verizon LG enV Touch.  I love the retractable construction of this charger -- it tucks neatly into the compartment that is now its home.  I know many people who've bought chargers for Verizon phones who then get messages on the phones saying the charger isn't recommended for the phone.  I'm always torn between believing those messages and wondering if it's just the company's way of pushing you to buy their own, more expensive products.  Doesn't matter here -- it isn't an issue for my phone with this charger -- it charges my phone rapidly & without any warning messages on the phone.  Shipping was also FAST and how can you beat free?  Great purchase!
I am so pleased with this charger.  It works great with my phone (LG VX8600) and it fits conveniently in my car, with no additional cord getting in the way.

The last thing I would label this is 'Professional'. It's easy enough to use, however it requires an included adapter to fit the G' zOne (or any other phone), and that is where the problem is. Being a car charger, just the movement of the car while driving causes it to lose it's connection to charge the phone. The wire doesn't come apart from the phone itself or from the adapter piece, it just loses it's connection at it's little adapter and the charge light goes off and the phone doesn't charge, even though you've connected it and all the while you think it's being charged. Very annoying. The slightest movement and the connection is compromised. Twisting the little connector or even touching the phone will get it charging again, then a minute later the connection is lost and the charge light is off again. Way too sensitive a connection. I bought this in August and it's now November and I would definitely NOT buy this again. It's cheap for a reason. About the only thing good (to date) I can offer is the wire retractor still works. Look elsewhere.Update: This "Professional Retractable Car Charger for LG G'zOne" has been disposed of. Total garbage.I'm convinced ANY chargers out there that requires adapters to make it work with your device, should be avoided at all costs. I learned my lesson; you get what you pay for.
summary: Professional Retractable Car Charger for LG G`zOne...

reviewText: My email to the seller:The first thing I see when I read about your company having the item is 'orders received by 10 a.m. ship overnight". Being pressed for time and needing the item fast and paying $19.03 to ship an item that weighs 3 ounces I had a reasonable expectation that it was possible and that the worst case would be it would ship the next day and would be received Thursday. Unfortunately I now have come to learn that orders received by 10 a.m. ship within 2 days or so and overnight actually means 1-2 days. The acceptable thing to do here is reduce the shipping charge to express rate and after that correct your advertisement copy to clearly explain your interpretation of of the term "overnight". The honorable thing to do would be to reduce the charge to your standard rate, apologize for the inconvenience.You can imaginewhat didn't happen? Their answer:If an order is placed on Tuesday for instance, and one day is paid, itis guaranteed to go out by Thursday and will arrive in one day from theshipment date.  99% of the time it goes out within 24 hours, as is thecase with yours.  Anything you can provide would be helpful, whetherit's our policy or Amazon stating differently.  One day shipping meansOne Day delivery from when it's been shipped, not One Day delivery fromthe second the order is placed. I wish your help on this so that I'msure its really clear by Amazon to all customers.The Lesson: Don't pay for overnight
summary: Since when does Overnight mean 4 days?

It's real frustrating to be in your car, talking to someone on your cellphone and a bluetooth tone signals a low battery. You're on a turnpike, miles away from a safe pull-over spot to continue conversation, so you have to resort to speakerphone, end the call, or chance getting a cell phone ticket in my state.Like my cellphone, I wanted security to charge my bluetooth when the A/C charger was not usable, so I purchased this item. For me, this charger has been a great investment. It's compact and you're able to pull out only as much cord as you need. When your done using it, retract the cord with no tangles and store it for the next use. The highlighting features are it's fast charge rate, and you can use the bluetooth while it's charging.Some users say that it looks "cheaply built". Maybe so in opinion, but this charger has worked well for me, flawlessly for 6 months. For the price of 2 loaves of bread, you can't go wrong -- especially with a lifetime guaranty. So if it breaks, I'm sure that Amazon will come to the rescue!
